{
  "stem": "4284.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the idea was that if you bombed German cities, why not the target that currently would be the most critical to cut off supplies to the occupied countries that Germany had occupied with World War II, including France?",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we suffered every day and every night.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Cologne was the first city to have daylight and nighttime bombing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What made it so incredible for Jews is that we were not allowed to seek shelter.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were not permitted to public shelters if you should happen to be on the street and an air raid was going on, nor could you go into the basement air shelter of your own apartment house.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They did, of course, and sometimes, because of panic, let us in because we panicked ourselves.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I would say 90% of the time, we had to stay in our one-room little place.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we did get bombed, not directly, but surrounding, which was very, very frightening.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And one time, we-- I woke up having been-- having fallen out of bed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I must say, what we call bed-- this wasn't a bed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This was just a little combination of slats upon which we put a pillow and a-- a blanket.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that was in the foot of the bed that my parents slept, also not quite a bed, but I mean, a lot closer.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And so the first time that we were sort of forced out of the bed by a very near hit, we tried to get in the air raid-- basement air raid shelter, and the people in the apartment house wouldn't even open the door.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So we returned back to our room.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But obviously, as you can see, we survived.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
